A robot can no more commit murder
than a human could walk on water.

243
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:14,670
Well, you know, there was
this one guy a long time ago.

244
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:28,680
- Stay back!
- Calm down, Detective.

245
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:32,390
The only thing dangerous
in this room is you.

246
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,900
Deactivate.

247
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:40,570
Look. lt's fine. What you're looking at
is the result of clever programming.

248
00:20:40,650 --> 00:20:43,490
An imitation of free will.
lt's nothing more.

249
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:46,160
Let's do an imitation
of protecting our asses.

250
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:49,700
Don't be absurd.
You were startled by a jack-in-the-box.

251
00:20:51,660 --> 00:20:53,580
- Deactivate.
- Let him go.

252
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,880
It's not going to hurt us.
I gave you an order.

253
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,460
He's not listening right now, lady.

254
00:20:58,540 --> 00:21:01,840
- VIKI, seal the lab!
- No, VIKI, leave the--

255
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:04,340
Command confirmed.

256
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,410
Police!

257
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:06,030
- You've hurt it... badly.
- Where's it going?

258
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:09,490
- Where?
- lt needs to repair itself.

259
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,910
John, l need backup.
l'm transmitting my location.

260
00:22:12,990 --> 00:22:15,330
- You don't need backup.
- That's nobody.

261
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:17,330
- What do you think you're doing?
- l'm driving.

262
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:20,500
- By hand?
- Do you see me on the phone?

263
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:23,340
- You can't be serious. Not at these speeds.
- John, please send the backup.

264
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:25,340
- Thank you.
- Try to listen, Detective.

265
00:22:25,420 --> 00:22:27,880
That robot is not going to harm us.

266
00:22:27,970 --> 00:22:29,890
Now, there must have been
unknown factors...

267
00:22:29,970 --> 00:22:32,930
but somehow, acting as it did,
kept us out of harm's way.

268
00:22:33,010 --> 00:22:35,140
A robot simply cannot
endanger a human being.

269
00:22:35,220 --> 00:22:37,940
Alert.

270
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:41,230
Aah! Asshole!

271
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:43,520
Which is more
than l can say for you.

272
00:22:44,820 --> 00:22:47,650
lt was a left,
by the way, back there.

273
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:51,160
You must know my ex-wife.

274
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:02,460
So, where is everybody?

275
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:05,960
This facility was designed, built
and is operated mechanically.

276
00:23:06,050 --> 00:23:10,180
No significant human presence
from inception to production.

277
00:23:10,260 --> 00:23:12,340
So, robots building robots.

278
00:23:12,430 --> 00:23:15,140
- Authorization code, please.
- Now that's just stupid.

279
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:17,470
I'm pulling up the inventory specs.

280
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:20,640
Our daily finishing capacity
is 1,000 NS-5s.

281
00:23:20,730 --> 00:23:24,230
I'm showing 1,001 .

282
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:43,960
Attention, NS-5s.

283
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:49,840
Well, you're the robot shrink.

284
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:55,720
There is a robot in this formation
that does not belong.

285
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:59,020
- ldentify it.
- One of us.

286
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:02,440
- Which one?
- One of us.

287
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:05,150
How much did you say
these things cost?

288
00:24:05,230 --> 00:24:07,980
Look. These NS-5s haven't been configured yet.
They're still just hardware.

289
00:24:08,070 --> 00:24:10,990
Basic Three Laws operating system.
That's it.

290
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:12,990
They don't know any better.

291
00:24:13,070 --> 00:24:14,950
What would you suggest?

292
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:19,450
lnterview each one. Cross-reference
their responses to detect any anomalies.

293
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:22,120
- How long would that take?
- About three weeks.

294
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:25,960
Okay. You go ahead
and get started.

295
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:33,300
Robots, you will not move.
Confirm command.

296
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:35,300
Command confirmed.

297
00:24:36,470 --> 00:24:38,720
Whoa. Detective,
what are you doing?

298
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:41,390
Well, you said they've all been
programmed with the Three Laws.

299
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,730
That means we have 1000 robots
that will not try to protect themselves...

300
00:24:43,810 --> 00:24:46,520
if it violates
a direct order from a human.

301
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:48,520
And I'm betting one who will.

302
00:24:48,610 --> 00:24:50,940
Detective, put your gun down.

303
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:53,240
Why do you give them faces?

304
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:55,570
Try to friendly them all up.
Make 'em look all human.

305
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:57,950
These robots are not susceptible
to intimidation.

306
00:24:58,030 --> 00:25:00,660
l guess if you didn't,
we wouldn't trust them.

307
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:02,710
- These robots are U.S.R. property.
- Not me.

308
00:25:02,790 --> 00:25:06,500
These things are just
lights and clockwork.

309
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,500
Are you crazy?

310
00:25:10,590 --> 00:25:12,670
Let me ask you something, Doc.

311
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,970
Does thinking you're the last sane man
on the face of the earth make you crazy?

312
00:25:16,050 --> 00:25:19,810
'Cause if it does, maybe l am.

313
00:25:24,140 --> 00:25:26,770
Gotcha.
Get the hell outta here!

314
00:25:44,660 --> 00:25:46,790
Detective!

315
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:13,360
- What am I?
- Can l help you, sir?

316
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,120
- There he is!
- Stay right where you are!

317
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:24,240
Deactivate at once!

318
00:26:24,330 --> 00:26:27,410
Obey the command.
Deactivate! Don't move!

319
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:30,540
Open fire!

320
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:48,810
- Hold your fire! Hold your fire!
- Easy!

321
00:26:48,890 --> 00:26:52,360
All units, stand down!

322
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:54,730
Please be advised, we're code four.

323
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:58,570
Code four. NS-5 is in custody.
NS-5 in custody.

324
00:27:00,740 --> 00:27:03,410
You have no idea what I had to go through
to clip this thing, John.

325
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:05,790
Yeah, l get it now. You actually think
you brought me something good.

326
00:27:05,870 --> 00:27:08,870
- That thing did it.
- Keep your voice down. Did what?

327
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,080
We have a suicide, Detective.
End of story.

328
00:27:11,170 --> 00:27:13,340
l am telling you
that robot killed him.

329
00:27:13,420 --> 00:27:15,340
And I'm telling you
that's impossible.

330
00:27:15,420 --> 00:27:19,220
And if it is possible, it sure as hell
better be in somebody else's precinct.

331
00:27:19,300 --> 00:27:21,470
John, John, give me
five minutes with it.

332
00:27:21,550 --> 00:27:24,180
What are you, nuts?
l just got off the phone with the D.A.

333
00:27:24,260 --> 00:27:27,140
Nobody goes into that room
until Robertson and his attorneys get here.

334
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:30,600
- What? No, this is my suspect.
- lt's a can opener, for Christ's sake.

335
00:27:30,690 --> 00:27:35,230
John, don't do this to me.
l am asking you for five minutes.

336
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,240
What if l'm right?

337
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:48,330
Well, then l guess we're gonna miss
the good old days.

338
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:50,250
What good old days?

339
00:27:50,330 --> 00:27:53,670
When people were killed
by other people.

340
00:28:01,010 --> 00:28:02,970
Five minutes.

341
00:28:30,790 --> 00:28:34,250
Murder's a new trick for a robot.
Congratulations.

342
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:38,500
Respond.

343
00:28:41,210 --> 00:28:44,130
What does this action signify?

344
00:28:44,220 --> 00:28:48,760
As you entered,
when you looked at the other human...

345
00:28:48,850 --> 00:28:51,220
what does it mean?

346
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,770
lt's a sign of trust.
lt's a human thing.

347
00:28:54,850 --> 00:28:57,440
You wouldn't understand.

348
00:28:57,520 --> 00:29:00,780
My father tried to
teach me human emotions.

349
00:29:00,860 --> 00:29:03,610
They are... difficult.

350
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:06,820
You mean your designer.

351
00:29:06,910 --> 00:29:09,200
Yes.

352
00:29:11,370 --> 00:29:13,410
So, why'd you murder him?

353
00:29:14,370 --> 00:29:16,290
l did not murder Dr. Lanning.

354
00:29:16,380 --> 00:29:19,420
Wanna explain why you were hiding
at the crime scene?

355
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:22,760
l was frightened.

356
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,260
Robots don't feel fear.

357
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:27,720
They don't feel anything.

358
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,720
They don't get hungry.
They don't sleep.

359
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:31,810
l do.

360
00:29:31,890 --> 00:29:34,310
l have even had dreams.

361
00:29:34,390 --> 00:29:36,980
Human beings have dreams.

362
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:39,270
Even dogs have dreams,
but not you.

363
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:43,190
You are just a machine.
An imitation of life.

364
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:47,780
Can a robot write a symphony?

365
00:29:47,860 --> 00:29:51,490
Can a robot turn a canvas
into a beautiful masterpiece?

366
00:29:51,580 --> 00:29:54,200
Can you?

367
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:04,010
l think you murdered him because he was
teaching you to simulate emotions...

368
00:30:04,090 --> 00:30:06,010
and things got out of control.

369
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:08,840
l did not murder him.

370
00:30:08,930 --> 00:30:12,510
But emotions don't seem
like a very useful simulation for a robot.

371
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:14,680
l did not murder him.

372
00:30:14,770 --> 00:30:18,520
Hell, l don't want my toaster
or my vacuum cleaner appearing emotional.

373
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:21,270
l did not murder him!

374
00:30:33,370 --> 00:30:36,410
That one's called "anger."

375
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,580
Ever simulate anger before?

376
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,840
Answer me, canner!

377
00:30:44,170 --> 00:30:46,130
My name is Sonny.

378
00:30:48,260 --> 00:30:50,470
So, we're naming you now.

379
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:54,470
ls that why you murdered him?

380
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,560
He made you angry?

381
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,770
Dr. Lanning killed himself.

382
00:31:00,190 --> 00:31:03,770
l don't know why
he wanted to die.

383
00:31:05,150 --> 00:31:07,110
l thought he was happy.

384
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:11,820
Maybe it was something
I did.

385
00:31:12,870 --> 00:31:14,660
Did I do something?

386
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:19,540
He asked me for a favor.
Made me promise.

387
00:31:19,620 --> 00:31:22,670
- What favor?
- Maybe l was wrong.

388
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,710
Maybe he was scared.

389
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:27,840
What are you talking about?
Scared of what?

390
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:32,590
You have to do what someone asks you.
Don't you, Detective Spooner?

391
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:36,350
- How the hell did you know my name?
- Don't you?

392
00:31:36,430 --> 00:31:39,810
lf you love them.

393
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:49,990
My robots don't kill people,
Lieutenant Bergin.

394
00:31:50,070 --> 00:31:52,950
My attorneys have filed
a brief with the D.A.

395
00:31:53,030 --> 00:31:56,410
He assures me a robot
cannot be charged with homicide.

396
00:31:56,490 --> 00:32:00,910
The brief confirms murder can only
be committed when one human kills another.

397
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:03,250
You of all people, Detective,
you're not suggesting...

398
00:32:03,330 --> 00:32:05,920
that this robot be treated
as human, are you?

399
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:11,300
Now granted, we can't rule out the robot's
proximity to the death of Dr. Lanning.

400
00:32:11,380 --> 00:32:14,140
Having said that, it's a machine.

401
00:32:14,220 --> 00:32:16,260
It's the property of U.S.R.

402
00:32:16,350 --> 00:32:19,600
At worst, that places this incident
firmly within the realm...

403
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:21,690
of an industrial accident.

404
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:24,860
As a matter of course, faulty machinery
will be returned to U.S.R....

405
00:32:24,940 --> 00:32:27,020
for diagnostics,
then decommissioned.

406
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:32,860
This is a gag order.
Now anyone in your department...

407
00:32:32,950 --> 00:32:35,660
so much as hinting
at the possibility of a killer robot...

408
00:32:35,740 --> 00:32:37,660
being apprehended by the police...

409
00:32:37,740 --> 00:32:40,370
will be deemed to be inciting
irrational panic.

410
00:32:40,450 --> 00:32:43,580
You'll be subject
to the full penalty of the law.

411
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:46,590
To hell with this guy, John.
Don't let him take this robot.

412
00:32:46,670 --> 00:32:49,670
- Spoon, we got nothing.
- This is some political bullshit.

413
00:32:49,750 --> 00:32:53,720
- Call the mayor.
- Lieutenant Bergin. His Honor, the mayor.

414
00:33:29,790 --> 00:33:34,010
In a bizarre turn, the rollout of U.S.R.'s
new generation of robots...

415
00:33:34,090 --> 00:33:36,300
was marred by the death
of Alfred Lanning...

416
00:33:36,380 --> 00:33:39,390
co-founder of the company
and designer of the NS-5.

417
00:33:39,470 --> 00:33:43,390
Dr. Lanning died early this morning
at U.S.R. headquarters.

418
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:46,230
The cause of death
is an apparent suicide.

419
00:33:46,310 --> 00:33:49,520
Your second round, sir.

420
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:51,520
Thank you.

421
00:33:51,610 --> 00:33:55,570
He founded U.S. Robotics, Inc. with
Lawrence Robertson in 2020...

422
00:33:55,650 --> 00:33:58,910
and launched the Nestor Class 1 robot--

