00:34:00,990 --> 00:34:02,910
This thing is
just like the Wolf Man.

425
00:34:02,990 --> 00:34:05,870
Uh-oh.
l'm really scared right now.

426
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:10,090
No, listen.
Guy creates monster.

427
00:34:10,170 --> 00:34:13,960
Monster kills guy.
Everybody kills monster. Wolf Man.

428
00:34:14,050 --> 00:34:16,510
That's Frankenstein.

429
00:34:16,590 --> 00:34:20,550
Frankenstein, Wolf Man, Dracula.
Shit, it's over. Case closed.

430
00:34:20,640 --> 00:34:23,010
Dr. Lanning
had a dream of a robot in every household.

431
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:28,020
- So, why the look?
- What look?

432
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:29,940
That look.

433
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:32,270
This is my face.
lt's not a look.

434
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:36,440
Good. Good.
No look is great.

435
00:34:36,530 --> 00:34:40,660
Only-- He was really quick
to wanna destroy it, wasn't he?

436
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:44,290
Well, what would you like him to do,
put a hat on it and stand on Michigan Avenue?

437
00:34:44,370 --> 00:34:47,080
- Come on. Let it go.
- What was the motive, John?

438
00:34:48,710 --> 00:34:50,960
Brother, it's a robot.

439
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:53,340
lt doesn't need a motive.
lt just has to be broken.

440
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:57,170
No. This thing looked like
it needed a motive.

441
00:34:57,260 --> 00:34:59,220
lt could have killed me, John.
Why didn't it just kill me?

442
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:01,760
All right, that's it.
You want me to call your grandmother?

443
00:35:01,850 --> 00:35:05,140
'Cause l will, you know.

444
00:35:05,220 --> 00:35:07,230
Yeah, l didn't think so.

445
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:10,150
Look. You were actually
right for once.

446
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:13,190
You are living proof
that it's better to be lucky than smart.

447
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:19,950
Come on.
The right guy for the right job.

448
00:35:22,410 --> 00:35:24,830
- What'd you say?
- Now what?

449
00:35:24,910 --> 00:35:26,870
Come on.
l'm giving you a compliment.

450
00:35:26,950 --> 00:35:29,910
Face it. With all the rocks you've been
looking under to find a bad robot...

451
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:33,000
what are the odds
you'd be the guy to find one?

452
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,630
Right. l wasn't just
the right guy for the job...

453
00:35:35,710 --> 00:35:38,420
- l was the perfect guy for the job.
- Damn right.

454
00:35:38,510 --> 00:35:41,130
What if I was supposed
to go for that robot?

455
00:35:41,220 --> 00:35:44,640
Oh, come on. Don't do this to yourself.
l'm begging you.

456
00:35:44,720 --> 00:35:47,810
The robot said that Lanning was scared.
What did he have to be scared of?

457
00:35:47,890 --> 00:35:51,980
l need a rain check.
Let me get this.

458
00:35:52,060 --> 00:35:54,730
- Total is 46.50. Thank you, Mr. Spooner.
- Spoon.

459
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:59,820
Nice shoes.

460
00:36:52,580 --> 00:36:57,710
- ldentify.
