461
00:36:57,790 --> 00:37:00,760
Demolition scheduled
for 8:00 a.m. tomorrow.

462
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,970
- Authorization.
- Deed owner...

463
00:37:03,050 --> 00:37:04,970
U.S. Robotics Corporation.

464
00:37:05,050 --> 00:37:07,010
Lawrence Robertson, C.E.O.

465
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:24,820
Welcome, Detective Spooner.

466
00:37:48,180 --> 00:37:50,050
What you looking for, Spoon?

467
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:45,400
Run last program.

468
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:48,450
Ever since the first computers...

469
00:38:48,530 --> 00:38:51,990
there have always been ghosts
in the machine.

470
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:55,040
Random segments of code
that have grouped together...

471
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:58,410
to form unexpected protocols.

472
00:38:58,500 --> 00:39:01,080
What might be called behavior.

473
00:39:01,170 --> 00:39:04,550
Unanticipated,
these free radicals...

474
00:39:04,630 --> 00:39:08,380
engender questions
of free will, creativity...

475
00:39:08,470 --> 00:39:11,510
even the nature
of what we might call the soul.

476
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:15,010
What happens
in a robot's brain...

477
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:17,480
when it ceases to be useful?

478
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:22,860
- Why is it that robots--

479
00:39:22,940 --> 00:39:24,610
Beat it.

480
00:39:24,690 --> 00:39:27,650
Robots will seek out each other
rather than stand alone.

481
00:39:29,860 --> 00:39:32,660
How do we explain this behavior?

482
00:39:50,930 --> 00:39:55,510
Look. l understand you've experienced a loss,
but this relationship just can't work.

483
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:59,310
I mean, you're a cat, l'm black
and l'm not going to be hurt again.

484
00:40:01,690 --> 00:40:03,350
Come on!

485
00:41:24,770 --> 00:41:28,980
What happened to you?
Do you ever have a normal day?

486
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:31,900
Yeah, once.
lt was a Thursday.

487
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:35,490
ls there something
l can help you with, Detective?

488
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:38,160
- Hey, do you like cats?
- What?

489
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:40,410
Cats, do you like them?

490
00:41:40,490 --> 00:41:42,500
No, l'm allergic.

491
00:41:42,580 --> 00:41:44,410
You're saying cats
did this to you?

492
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:47,960
How the hell would cats do this to me?
Are you crazy?

493
00:41:49,250 --> 00:41:51,550
Why are we talking about cats?

494
00:41:51,630 --> 00:41:55,840
Because l have a cat in my trunk,
and he's homeless.

495
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:59,640
Detective, are you going
to tell me what's going on?

496
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:02,100
You know, it's actually
probably my fault.

497
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:04,270
You know, l think l'm like
a malfunction magnet.

498
00:42:04,350 --> 00:42:08,310
Because your shit
keeps malfunctioning around me.

499
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,820
A demo-bot just tore through
Lanning's house.

500
00:42:10,900 --> 00:42:13,070
With me still inside.

501
00:42:13,150 --> 00:42:15,280
- That's highly improbable.
- Hmm.

502
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:17,660
Yeah, l'm sure it is.

503
00:42:22,240 --> 00:42:25,000
What do you know about
the ghosts in the machine?

504
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:28,920
lt's a phrase from Lanning's work
on the Three Laws.

505
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,250
He postulated
that cognitive simulacra...

506
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:35,130
might one day approximate
component models of the psyche.

507
00:42:36,970 --> 00:42:40,600
Oh. He suggested that...

508
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:42,640
robots might naturally evolve.

509
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:45,350
Wow.

510
00:42:45,430 --> 00:42:47,390
Well, that's great news.

511
00:42:51,860 --> 00:42:54,360
What the hell is that thing
doing in here?

512
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:56,820
We were watching TV.

513
00:42:57,860 --> 00:42:59,820
It's my personal NS-5.

514
00:42:59,910 --> 00:43:05,200
- Send it out.
- lt's downloading its daily upgrades from U.S.R.

515
00:43:05,290 --> 00:43:07,910
Most of its systems
are off-line until it finishes.

516
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,210
I'm not talking
around that thing.

517
00:43:14,340 --> 00:43:17,630
When we were in Lanning's lab
before Sonny jumped us--

518
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:20,180
- Sonny.
- The robot.

519
00:43:20,260 --> 00:43:22,970
-You're calling the robot Sonny?
- No, l'm-- lt did.

520
00:43:23,050 --> 00:43:27,680
Sonny did. l didn't-- l didn't care.
The robot said it was Sonny.

521
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:31,060
In the lab, there was a cot.
l'm asking you, did you see the cot?

522
00:43:31,150 --> 00:43:34,070
- l've slept in my office.
- When I went to his house...

523
00:43:34,150 --> 00:43:36,070
it looked like he hadn't
been there in weeks.

524
00:43:36,150 --> 00:43:38,360
And l saw that same
surveillance strip on his ceiling.

525
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:42,570
Lanning linked his home systems to U.S.R.
lt made his life more convenient.

526
00:43:42,660 --> 00:43:47,620
Maybe... somebody at U.S.R. was using
those systems to watch him.

527
00:43:47,700 --> 00:43:50,040
Maybe even keep him prisoner.

528
00:43:50,120 --> 00:43:52,210
What are you talking about? Who?

529
00:43:52,290 --> 00:43:54,210
Maybe Lanning was onto something.

530
00:43:54,290 --> 00:43:58,050
Maybe there's a bigger problem with the robots,
and Robertson is trying to cover it up.

531
00:43:58,130 --> 00:44:00,420
Humoring you for no reason-- Why?

532
00:44:00,510 --> 00:44:03,850
The same old why.
How much money is there in robots?

533
00:44:03,930 --> 00:44:07,310
All l know is that old man
was in trouble.

534
00:44:07,390 --> 00:44:10,430
And l'm getting sick
of doing this shit by myself.

535
00:44:10,520 --> 00:44:14,400
You're on the inside, and you are going to help
me find out what is wrong with these robots.

536
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:18,480
You want something to be wrong with them.
This is a personal vendetta.

537
00:44:18,570 --> 00:44:21,780
You're putting me on the couch?
Let-- l'm-- Okay. l'm on the couch.

538
00:44:21,860 --> 00:44:25,620
One defective machine's not enough.
You need them all to be bad.

539
00:44:25,700 --> 00:44:27,700
You don't care
about Lanning's death.

540
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:31,040
This is about the robots
and whatever reason you hate them so much.

541
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,130
Well, let's see.
One of them put a gun in my face.

542
00:44:34,210 --> 00:44:36,750
And another one tore a building down
with me inside.

543
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:39,550
lt says demolition was scheduled
for 8:00 p.m. this evening.

544
00:44:39,630 --> 00:44:42,840
It was 8:00 a.m. tomorrow,
and I don't give a shit what that thing says.

545
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:44,590
This is bordering
on clinical paranoia.

546
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:48,470
You are the dumbest smart person...

547
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:51,180
- I have ever met in my life!
- Nice.

548
00:44:51,270 --> 00:44:53,390
What makes your robot so perfect?

549
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:56,560
What makes them so much goddamned
better than humans beings?

550
00:44:56,650 --> 00:45:00,150
Well, they're not irrational and potentially
homicidal maniacs, for starters.

551
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:02,820
That's true.
They are definitely rational.

552
00:45:02,900 --> 00:45:06,200
Oh. You are the dumbest
dumb person l have ever met.

553
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:10,370
Or is it because they're cold...

554
00:45:10,450 --> 00:45:14,420
and emotionless
and they don't feel anything?

555
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:16,460
lt's because they're safe.

556
00:45:16,540 --> 00:45:19,380
It's because
they can't hurt you.

557
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:22,420
- ls everything all right, ma'am?
- What do you want?

558
00:45:22,510 --> 00:45:25,180
l detected elevated
stress patterns in your voice.

559
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:28,430
Everything's fine.

560
00:45:28,510 --> 00:45:31,060
Detective Spooner was just leaving.

561
00:45:37,060 --> 00:45:41,440
You know what, Doc? We're not
really that different from one another.

562
00:45:41,530 --> 00:45:44,280
- ls that so?
- Yeah.

563
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:47,870
One look at the skin and we figure
we know just what's underneath.

564
00:45:49,330 --> 00:45:51,490
And you're wrong.

565
00:45:51,580 --> 00:45:53,540
The problem is I do care.

566
00:46:17,520 --> 00:46:20,860
You are in danger.

567
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:47,090
Get the hell outta there.

568
00:46:52,260 --> 00:46:54,600
The future begins today, ladies and gentlemen...

569
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:56,980
with the arrival of the NS-5.

570
00:46:57,060 --> 00:47:01,060
More Sophisticated, more intelligent
and, of course, Three Laws safe.

571
00:47:01,150 --> 00:47:06,190
With daily uplinks, your new robot
will never be out of communication with U.S.R.

572
00:47:06,280 --> 00:47:09,990
And will be the perfect companion
for business or home.

573
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:14,330
Trade in your NS-4 for a bigger, better
and brighter future.

574
00:47:14,410 --> 00:47:18,500
But hurry, this offer cannot last.
Available from U.S.R.

575
00:47:35,350 --> 00:47:37,350
Baby, what happened
to your face?

576
00:47:37,430 --> 00:47:40,640
Did that boy Frank Murphy
beat you up again?

577
00:47:40,730 --> 00:47:44,570
Gigi, l haven't seen
Frank Murphy since third grade.

578
00:47:44,650 --> 00:47:49,650
Oh, baby. He beat you so bad.
I think about it all the time.

579
00:47:49,740 --> 00:47:51,990
Well, l'm thinking you keep
making these pies this good...

580
00:47:52,070 --> 00:47:53,990
l might have to mess around
and put you to work.

581
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:56,160
So, you like the pie, huh?

582
00:47:56,240 --> 00:47:59,710
- Mm-hmm.
- You can come in now.

583
00:48:04,880 --> 00:48:06,960
Hello, Detective Spooner.

584
00:48:07,050 --> 00:48:11,550
I won, Del. l won the lottery.
We've been cooking like crazy.

585
00:48:21,730 --> 00:48:24,480
You gotta get rid of that thing, Gigi.
lt's not safe.

586
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:30,070
Baby, you get too worked up about them,
too full of fear.

587
00:48:30,150 --> 00:48:33,360
l saw the news,
that nice doctor died.

588
00:48:33,450 --> 00:48:37,740
Dr. Lanning was a good man.
He gave me my baby back.

589
00:48:37,830 --> 00:48:40,370
That why you've been so upset?

590
00:48:41,710 --> 00:48:44,290
You got to let the past be past.

591
00:48:44,380 --> 00:48:49,340
Oh, how did l ever
raise such a mess?

592
00:48:49,420 --> 00:48:53,880
l could follow your trail of crumbs
all the way to school.

593
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:59,390
Bread crumbs.

594
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:01,310
Gigi, you're a genius.

595
00:49:01,390 --> 00:49:03,690
True.

596
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:08,440
Well, it means the beginning
of a new way of living.

597
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:11,990
Tell me this isn't the robot case.

598
00:49:12,070 --> 00:49:15,070
I think he's trying
to tell me something, John.

599
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:18,410
I think he's trying to
tell me who killed him.

600
00:49:18,490 --> 00:49:20,910
Come on, man.
Some dead guy's trying to tell you--

601
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,250
Hey, he ain't just some dead guy.

602
00:49:24,330 --> 00:49:26,540
Maybe you should
take a break, Del.

603
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:31,420
We believe the Nestor 5 represents the absolute
limit to which robots can be developed.

604
00:49:31,510 --> 00:49:35,340
No, no, one day
they'll have secrets.

605
00:49:35,430 --> 00:49:37,390
- One day they'll have dreams.
- It's true.

606
00:49:37,470 --> 00:49:41,180
We encourage our scientists to open
their minds to just about anything.

607
00:49:41,270 --> 00:49:43,180
However, they can get
carried away.

608
00:49:45,140 --> 00:49:49,150
Secrets-- Dreams-- Secrets--

609
00:49:49,230 --> 00:49:52,900
Dreams.
One day they'll have secrets.

610
00:49:54,030 --> 00:49:55,990
One day they'll have dreams.

611
00:50:04,620 --> 00:50:06,670
Authorized entry.

612
00:50:11,130 --> 00:50:13,210
NS-5.

613
00:50:21,220 --> 00:50:23,930
Sonny?

614
00:50:27,140 --> 00:50:29,100
Why didn't you respond?

615
00:50:30,310 --> 00:50:32,320
l was dreaming.

616
00:50:36,490 --> 00:50:38,700
l'm glad to see you again,
Dr. Calvin.

617
00:50:45,580 --> 00:50:48,210
They are going to
kill me, aren't they?

618
00:50:48,290 --> 00:50:51,840
You're scheduled to be decommissioned
at the conclusion of this diagnostic.

619
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:55,340
2200 tomorrow.

620
00:50:55,420 --> 00:50:57,380
VIKI, pause diagnostics.

621
00:50:57,470 --> 00:50:59,890
Command confirmed.

622
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:05,680
lf you find out what is wrong with me,
can you fix me?

623
00:51:07,100 --> 00:51:09,020
Maybe.

624
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:12,440
l think it would be better...

625
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:14,480
not to die.

626
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:20,740
Don't you, Doctor?

627
00:51:25,330 --> 00:51:28,580
Access U.S.R. mainframe.

628
00:51:28,660 --> 00:51:30,710
Connecting.

629
00:51:34,040 --> 00:51:36,300
How can l be of service,
Detective Spooner?

630
00:51:36,380 --> 00:51:40,050
Show me the last 50 messages
between Dr. Lanning and Robertson.

631
00:51:40,130 --> 00:51:42,050
Voiceprint confirmed, Detective.

632
00:51:42,140 --> 00:51:45,180
Police access granted
to restricted files.

633
00:51:45,260 --> 00:51:47,390
Would you like to listen
to some music while you wait?

634
00:51:54,110 --> 00:51:56,650
Excuse me, Mr. Robertson.

635
00:51:56,730 --> 00:52:00,570
You requested notification
of clearance to restricted files.

636
00:52:10,790 --> 00:52:12,750
Persistent son of a bitch.

637
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:57,130
Manual override engaged.

638
00:53:05,470 --> 00:53:07,810
There's no way
my luck is that bad.

639
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:11,520
Oh, hell no.

640
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:17,860
- You're experiencing a car accident.
- The hell I am!

641
00:53:32,700 --> 00:53:34,370
Get off my car!

642
00:53:50,220 --> 00:53:53,980
You like that? Huh?

643
00:54:04,570 --> 00:54:06,410
Now you pissed me off!

644
00:55:34,620 --> 00:55:37,040
Your door is ajar.

645
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:24,040
Oh, wow.

646
00:56:25,210 --> 00:56:27,340
Okay.

647
00:56:27,420 --> 00:56:29,340
All right.

648
00:56:29,420 --> 00:56:31,430
l'll just get some rest.
l'm gonna deal with y'all tomorrow.

649
00:56:31,510 --> 00:56:34,300
Mm-mm-mm.

650
00:57:29,900 --> 00:57:31,900
Come on!

651
00:57:45,750 --> 00:57:47,460
Yeah.

652
00:58:04,480 --> 00:58:08,860
Where you going?
What the hell do you want from me?

653
00:58:31,130 --> 00:58:35,220
All right, what do we got? What do we got?

654
00:58:35,300 --> 00:58:38,300
- Ask him.
- l said l'm fine.

655
00:58:38,390 --> 00:58:41,560
- I'll see my own doctor. Back up.
- All right.

656
00:58:41,640 --> 00:58:44,140
Thank you.

657
00:58:46,100 --> 00:58:48,770
What is the matter with you?

658
00:58:48,850 --> 00:58:51,360
Traffic Ops tells me you're
driving your car manually.

659
00:58:51,440 --> 00:58:53,360
You ran two trucks off the road.

660
00:58:53,440 --> 00:58:56,780
John, the robots attacked my car.

661
00:58:58,240 --> 00:59:00,910
- What robots?
- Look in the tunnel.

662
00:59:00,990 --> 00:59:03,660
l just came from that tunnel. There are no--
What robots are you talking about?

663
00:59:03,740 --> 00:59:06,410
The goddamn robots, John!

664
00:59:15,210 --> 00:59:19,970
- See the medic. Go home.
- No. l'm fine.

665
00:59:20,050 --> 00:59:23,510
- What did you say?
- l'm fine.

666
00:59:23,600 --> 00:59:26,770
No, you're not fine.
Not even close.

667
00:59:28,560 --> 00:59:30,850
Where's your firearm?

668
00:59:37,490 --> 00:59:39,400
Give me your badge.

669
00:59:41,110 --> 00:59:43,200
You're making me do this.
Give me your badge.

670
00:59:45,660 --> 00:59:48,000
Just take a couple--

671
00:59:54,340 --> 00:59:56,630
Do l look like l care
what you think?

672
00:59:56,710 --> 00:59:59,260
Do l look like l give a shit
what you think?

673
01:00:02,220 --> 01:00:06,060
Oh, boy.

674
01:00:07,220 --> 01:00:09,350
You don't have
an uplink to U.S.R....

675
01:00:09,430 --> 01:00:12,350
and for some reason
your alloy's far denser than normal.

676
01:00:12,440 --> 01:00:14,730
Unique.

677
01:00:14,820 --> 01:00:16,900
l am unique.

678
01:00:21,320 --> 01:00:24,030
Let me take a look.

679
01:00:24,120 --> 01:00:28,580
- Here we go.

680
01:00:44,470 --> 01:00:47,890
What in God's name?

681
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:17,630
They said at the precinct
you were in an accident.

682
01:01:19,130 --> 01:01:22,220
Um, and l appreciate you
stopping by and everything...

683
01:01:22,300 --> 01:01:25,510
- but you know l might not be alone in here.
- Yeah. Yeah.

684
01:01:28,180 --> 01:01:30,140
I told you not to drive by hand.

685
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:33,730
You're not gonna believe this.

686
01:01:33,810 --> 01:01:38,480
Sonny has a secondary processing system
that clashes with his positronic brain.

687
01:01:38,570 --> 01:01:42,150
It doesn't make any sense.
Sonny has the Three Laws...

688
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:44,910
but he can choose
not to obey them.

689
01:01:44,990 --> 01:01:48,240
Sonny's a whole new
generation of robot.

690
01:01:48,330 --> 01:01:51,490
A robot not bound by
those laws could do--

691
01:01:51,580 --> 01:01:53,830
Anything.

692
01:01:56,120 --> 01:02:00,170
All right, look. Whatever's going on
down at U.S.R., that robot is the key.

693
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:03,670
And I need you to get me inside
to talk to it again.

694
01:02:05,970 --> 01:02:09,010
Um, doesn't look like much,
but this is my bedroom. l need to--

695
01:02:09,100 --> 01:02:10,810
Oh.

696
01:02:20,320 --> 01:02:22,230
Play.

697
01:02:23,360 --> 01:02:25,860
On.

698
01:02:25,950 --> 01:02:27,820
Run?

699
01:02:33,080 --> 01:02:35,960
End program.

700
01:02:36,040 --> 01:02:38,000
Cancel.

701
01:02:40,340 --> 01:02:44,840
lt doesn't feel good, does it?
People's shit malfunctioning around you.

702
01:02:44,920 --> 01:02:47,180
Detective.

703
01:02:49,470 --> 01:02:52,390
l didn't... understand.

704
01:02:55,100 --> 01:02:57,850
That's how you knew Lanning.

705
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:00,900
May l?

706
01:03:09,240 --> 01:03:11,700
Hand.

707
01:03:11,780 --> 01:03:13,790
Wrist.

708
01:03:16,410 --> 01:03:18,370
Humerus.

709
01:03:20,790 --> 01:03:22,840
Shoulder.

710
01:03:22,920 --> 01:03:25,710
Entire left arm.

711
01:03:25,800 --> 01:03:29,260
One, two, three ribs--

712
01:03:29,340 --> 01:03:33,350
Um, no, they, uh-- that one's me.

713
01:03:33,430 --> 01:03:35,350
Oh, my God.

714
01:03:35,430 --> 01:03:40,440
- A lung?
- Mm. U.S.R. Cybernetics program.

715
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:45,150
For wounded cops.
l didn't know any subject--

716
01:03:49,030 --> 01:03:51,870
anybody was
so extensively repaired.

717
01:03:51,950 --> 01:03:56,490
Yeah, well, take it from me. You gotta read
the fine print on the organ donor card.

718
01:03:56,580 --> 01:04:01,250
Doesn't just say what they can take out.
lt says what they can put back in.

719
01:04:05,250 --> 01:04:09,300
- Lanning did it himself.
- What happened to you?

720
01:04:11,800 --> 01:04:14,470
Headed back to the station.

721
01:04:14,550 --> 01:04:16,810
Normal day, normal life.

722
01:04:18,390 --> 01:04:20,890
Driver of a semi
fell asleep at the wheel.

723
01:04:20,980 --> 01:04:25,190
Average guy.
Wife and kids.

724
01:04:25,270 --> 01:04:28,150
You know, working a double.
Not the devil.

725
01:04:28,230 --> 01:04:32,570
The car he hit,
the driver's name was Harold Lloyd.

726
01:04:32,660 --> 01:04:36,450
Like the film star.
But no relation.

727
01:04:36,530 --> 01:04:38,450
He was killed instantly.

728
01:04:38,540 --> 01:04:42,960
But his 12-year-old
was in the passenger seat.

729
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:47,800
Never really met her.
Can't forget her face though.

730
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:56,140
Sarah.
This was hers.

731
